contentrichtext.text: {{Wiktionary}} '''Jammer''' may refer to: * [[Jammer keyboard]] * Jammer, a device used in [[radar jamming and deception]] and [[Communications System Jamming]], a technique in electronic warfare to inhibit or halt the transmission of signals * [[Mobile phone jammer]], an instrument used to prevent cellular phones from receiving signals from base stations. * [[Swim jammer]], a type of male competitive swimwear * [[Max Jammer]], a noted physicist in the 20th century * [[Jammer (Battlestar Galactica)]], a character in the TV series Battlestar Galactica * The red buses used to shuttle guests around [[Glacier National Park (U.S.)|Glacier National Park]] * [[Jammer (mascot)]], mascot of the Northern League Joliet Jackhammers * A player for the [[Jamestown Jammers]] minor league baseball team * Jammer, the scoring position in [[Roller derby]] * [[Quentin Jammer]], a cornerback for the San Diego Chargers * [[Jammer (rapper)]], a UK grime MC * Jammer ([[Jammer Direct]]), a member of the Social Networking Site [[Jammer Direct]] * Jammers, a group of characters in the TV series ''[[The Prisoner]]'' who use misdirection to confuse onlookers with misinformation * [[Jammer (Sailing)]], a mechanical fitting with a lever arm that cleats a rope. * [[Um Jammer Lammy]], a rhythm video game for the [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] * [[Jammer (Artist,Host)]], a copyrighted artist and co-host of "[[The Spit or Swallow Beer Review]]" with Shagdog from www.mytrurevu.com and on YouTube channel named "[[mytrurevu]]" {{disambig}}
